            {
               "text": "#### Conclusion\n\nIn this text, we saw that there are different ways to express a traveled path. Regardless of the approach used, the horizontal and vertical displacements are treated independently, although both represent the total distance traveled.\n\nFurthermore, we observed, through the Pythagorean Theorem, that the relationships between the projections of the hypotenuse onto its legs can also be described using the cosine and sine of the angle formed between the hypotenuse and the horizontal.",
